          "title": "NEXT UP FOR CRISPR: GENE EDITING FOR THE MASSES?",
          "summary": "Advances in CRISPR technology may soon make it possible for a vaccine that provides lifelong protection against heart disease. New forms of the technology, like prime editing, are broadening the scope of gene-editing treatments. They can be used to target diseases that aren't caused by rogue genes. An approach currently in testing to lower blood cholesterol could one day be used to protect people from high blood pressure and diabetes.",
